</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The image is printed over the leading edge 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Part of the image is printed on the platen instead of the media 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-BBA78FCD-BA91-477F-8DA4-BFF1E3005A7E" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available which can pinpoint to this case.
</p></section><section id="GUID-A0DD5BBC-D07D-4E38-9A80-FA9FA935A570" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No available ADAM-triggers 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-747DD962-6AE5-4316-8F0C-5BDB203BE17D" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-12A1BCA6-20DA-4A13-A0E7-0C0FD6148B71-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-12A1BCA6-20DA-4A13-A0E7-0C0FD6148B71-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the media was cut straight. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">When loading the media use the “Clean cut” option in the UI. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if artifact is present on other media with the same width. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use other media. The current media might be to “slippery” 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the X-tran wheels 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15DISA001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D2422B11-B63C-4FEC-AA37-86683DEF45CA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch?>15 How to remove the rollers of the Xtran pinch</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">When loading a roll of media into the printer. Always make sure the media is cut straight. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">When media is loaded onto the platen it is flushed to the end of the platen. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After option cutting the media is retracted by the X-tran rollers to its starting position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the media shows some slip in the X-tran pinch it’s possible the media is retracted too much. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In such case the image will be printed over the leading edge and will pollute the platen and the backside of the media.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-00803BE3-C849-4315-B1B2-2BBE04B8DBA4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
